{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"FP New acceptors shows that from From July 2023 to February 2025, new family planning acceptor volumes show moderate fluctuations but remain largely stable over time. After peaking near 60,000 in mid‑2023, volumes decline to about 50,000 in late 2023, representing a brief dip rather than a major downturn. 

The Uptake recovers in early 2024 and stabilizes within a consistent 55,000–63,000 range throughout the year, reflecting steady demand and service availability. By early 2025, volumes remain aligned with late‑2024 levels. 

Overall, the trend indicates stable utilization with no dramatic shifts, and the observed variations likely reflect normal seasonal, operational, or reporting dynamics.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":0.8,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"1ef7a30f-ef19-4fe7-ba79-c2c2c5c8d578","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"replicateBy":"indicator_common_id","selectedReplicantValue":"new_fp"}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in New family planning acceptors","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

